ized by the korean schools association of northern california ksanc shin pointed to the connection between language and identity emphasizing the importance of developing korean language skills in children of korean ethnicity growing up in the united states he noted the dual significance of having a strong well rounded korean american identity one rooted in a solid understanding of korean language culture and history with also a firm sense of being american ksanc is a non profit organization dedicated to providing korean language instruction and programming about korean culture and history to children and adults through its outreach activities stanford ksp helps to support the mission of ksanc and numerous other non profit education organizations throughout northern california html+ read more korea daily korean schools association of northern california working hard to improve educational standards korean language http www koreadaily com news read search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest leif eric easley discusses issues of korean and us identity in the news korean studies institute university of southern california on february 10 2011 issues of history values memory and identity in the us south korea relationship december 6 2010 ksp news contemplating korean reunification peter m beck wall street journal on january 4 2010 north korea and contending south korean identities analysis of the south korean media policy implications for the united states may 9 2007 ksp news the korean studies program at shorenstein aparc welcomes a new korean language librarian january 31 2007 shorenstein aparc fsi stanford ksp news the korean studies program welcomes a new postdoctoral fellow and its first korean language librarian september 13 2005 ksp news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 